# What is mAIcelium

mAIcelium is a multi-IDE, multi-project AI workspace orchestration framework.
Its goal is to let multiple AI agents (Claude Code, Cursor, Antigravity) collaborate
on multiple software projects simultaneously, with a single source of truth for
AI configuration.

## Core idea

A central private repository (`mAIcelium-private`) acts as the **control plane**:
- It holds all AI rules, skills, commands, prompts, and MCP definitions under `mesh/`.
- Real project repositories connect as **symlinks** under `projects/`.
- IDE-specific dotfolders (`.cursor/`, `.claude/`, `.agents/`) are auto-generated
  mirrors of `mesh/` — they are never edited directly.

```
mAIcelium/
├── mesh/              ← Single source of truth for all AI config
│   ├── rules/         ← Rules injected into every agent context
│   ├── skills/        ← Operational playbooks agents can follow
│   ├── commands/      ← Slash commands + Python scripts
│   ├── prompts/       ← Reusable prompt templates
│   └── mcp/           ← MCP server definitions (IDE-agnostic)
├── projects/          ← Symlinks to real project repos on disk
├── repos/
│   └── _registry.yaml ← Index of all available repos (check before /add_project)
├── bin/               ← Workspace management scripts
│   ├── init.sh           ← One-time workspace setup
│   ├── add_project.sh    ← Link a new project repo
│   ├── remove_project.sh ← Unlink a project repo
│   ├── sync_symlinks.sh  ← Regenerate all dotfolder mirrors + MCP configs
│   ├── separate_git.sh   ← Move .git out of workspace root (separated git mode)
│   ├── _lib.sh           ← Shared bash library for all scripts
│   └── hooks/
│       ├── guard-bash.sh   ← PreToolUse: blocks dangerous shell commands
│       └── guard-write.sh  ← PreToolUse: blocks writes to protected files
├── WORKSPACE.md       ← Auto-generated: active projects + their inlined rules
└── CLAUDE.md          ← Claude Code entry point
```

## The three-IDE model

| IDE          | Role                               | Primary strength          |
|--------------|------------------------------------|---------------------------|
| Claude Code  | Planning, architecture, analysis   | Long-context reasoning    |
| Cursor       | Code implementation                | Inline edits, Agent mode  |
| Antigravity  | Refactoring, review, scoped tasks  | Focused transformations   |

Each IDE runs independently but reads the same rules and skills from `mesh/`.

## How rules and skills reach agents

1. `bin/sync_symlinks.sh` (runs on every `SessionStart`) regenerates symlinks from
   `mesh/rules/` and `mesh/skills/` into each IDE's dotfolder.
2. Rules with `alwaysApply: true` are injected automatically into every agent context.
3. Skills are on-demand playbooks — agents read the relevant `SKILL.md` before a task.
4. `.claude/projects-context.md` is a pre-inlined version of all active project rules,
   generated for Claude Code.

## Available slash commands

These commands are defined in `mesh/commands/` and available in all IDEs:

| Command | Script | Purpose |
|---------|--------|---------|
| `/add_project <name>` | `scripts/add_project.py` | Fuzzy-match registry, link project repo |
| `/remove_project <name>` | `scripts/remove_project.py` | Unlink a project repo |
| `/list_projects` | `scripts/list_projects.py` | Show all linked projects |
| `/workspace_status` | `scripts/list_projects.py` | Full workspace state overview |
| `/project_health` | `scripts/project_health.py` | Diagnostic health check across projects |
| `/git_backup [msg]` | bash (bin/) | Stage, commit, push workspace changes |

Always check `repos/_registry.yaml` before running `/add_project` — it lists all
available repos with their paths and tech stacks.

## Safety hooks (PreToolUse)

Two hooks run automatically before every tool call in Claude Code:

**`guard-bash.sh`** blocks shell commands that:
- Use `rm -rf` targeting root, home, or wildcard paths (safe targets like `node_modules` are allowed)
- Execute destructive SQL (`DROP TABLE`, `TRUNCATE`)

**`guard-write.sh`** blocks writes/edits to:
- `.env` files (may contain secrets)
- `.git/` internals
- Auto-generated files: `WORKSPACE.md`, `mAIcelium.code-workspace`, `.claude/projects-context.md`
- Agent settings: `.claude/settings.json`, `.claude/settings.local.json`
- Auto-generated dotfolders: `.cursor/`, `.antigravity/`
- Lockfiles: `package-lock.json`, `yarn.lock`, `poetry.lock`, etc.

If a tool call is blocked by a hook, the reason will be shown. The fix is always to
target `mesh/` instead of the protected path, or use the appropriate `bin/` script.

## Separated git mode

`bin/separate_git.sh` moves `.git` out of the workspace root into a sibling directory
(`mAIcelium-git-backup/`). This prevents Cursor from treating the workspace root as a
git repo and showing all project files as uncommitted changes.

When separated git mode is active, all git commands on the workspace must use:
```bash
git --git-dir=../mAIcelium-git-backup/.git --work-tree=. <command>
```
The `/git_backup` command handles this automatically. Never run bare `git` commands
in the workspace root if `.git` is absent.

## Project lifecycle

```
# Link a new repo
bin/add_project.sh <name>        → creates symlink in projects/, updates WORKSPACE.md

# Remove a linked repo
bin/remove_project.sh <name>     → removes symlink, updates WORKSPACE.md

# Rebuild all mirrors after any mesh/ change
bin/sync_symlinks.sh             → regenerates .cursor/, .claude/, .agents/, .mcp.json
```

## What agents must never do

- Edit anything in `.cursor/`, `.claude/`, or `.agents/` — they are auto-generated.
- Run `rm -rf` on symlink targets inside `projects/` — that destroys the real repo.
- Create AI resources (rules, skills, commands) outside of `mesh/`.
- Act on projects not listed in `WORKSPACE.md`.
- Run bare `git` commands in the workspace root when separated git mode is active.
- Modify `WORKSPACE.md` or `.claude/projects-context.md` by hand — use `bin/` scripts.
